Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 805/68 of 27 June 1968 on the common organization of the market in beef and veal (1), as last amended by Commission Regulation (EC) No 2417/95 (2), and in particular Articles 9, 13 and 25 thereof,
Whereas Commission Regulation (EC) No 251/96 (3) temporarily derogated from Commission Regulation (EC) No 1445/95 (4), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 2856/95 (5), which lays down rules of application for import and export licences in the beef and veal sector;
Whereas the reasons that led to the reduction of the period of validity for export licences with advance fixing of the refund continue to exist; whereas it is therefore necessary to extend the duration of the validity of Regulation (EC) No 251/96;
Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Beef and Veal,
